Deputy National Security Advisor Mike Froman gave a press briefing on the upcoming G20 summit. He discussed the importance of international cooperation during times of economic crisis and highlighted the agenda for the summit, which includes restoring growth and regulatory reform. He also mentioned the progress that has already been made since the last G20 summit in November, such as stimulus plans and efforts to resist protectionism. Froman stated that the U.S. is prepared to lead and fulfill the agenda for international cooperation. He also mentioned that there will be bilateral meetings with leaders from China and Russia, and that the G20 format is important for addressing the economic and financial crisis. The briefing concluded with a discussion on the role of the IMF in monitoring stimulus efforts and the possibility of future G20 meetings.